kubectl top pods

ğŸš€ Advanced kubectl Commands (Production Level)
ğŸ“Œ Debugging & Troubleshooting
kubectl get events --sort-by=.metadata.creationTimestamp
kubectl logs <pod-name> --previous
kubectl describe pod <pod-name> | grep -i error


Ephemeral debug container:

kubectl debug pod/<pod-name> -it --image=busybox

ğŸ“Œ JSON & YAML Output
kubectl get pod <pod-name> -o yaml
kubectl get pod <pod-name> -o json


Using JSONPath:

kubectl get pods -o jsonpath='{.items[*].metadata.name}'

ğŸ“Œ Label & Annotation Management
kubectl label pod <pod-name> app=frontend
kubectl annotate pod <pod-name> owner=devops

ğŸ“Œ RBAC & Security
